print(f"{theta_deg}{chr(176)}")
âœ… What it does:
Uses f-string formatting to insert the value of theta_deg into the string.

chr(176) is the ASCII-safe way to print the degree symbol (Â°).

In Python, chr() returns the character associated with an ASCII code.

chr(176) = Â° (degree symbol).

ğŸ’¡ This avoids directly typing Â°, which may be considered non-ASCII and cause errors on some coding platforms.
